{"id":77147,"title":"Salvaging hope: Is increasing NAD(+) a key to treating mitochondrial myopathy?","abstract":"Mitochondrial diseases can arise from mutations either in mitochondrial DNA or in nuclear DNA encoding mitochondrially destined proteins. Currently, there is no cure for these diseases although treatments to ameliorate a subset of the symptoms are being developed. In this issue of EMBO Molecular Medicine, Khan et al (2014) use a mouse model to test the efficacy of a simple dietary supplement of nicotinamide riboside to treat and prevent mitochondrial myopathies.","date":"2014-06-04","categories":"Nutritional and Metabolic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24838280","annotations":[{"name":"Dietary supplement","weight":0.867658,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dietary_supplement"},{"name":"Nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide","weight":0.861965,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicotinamide_adenine_dinucleotide"},{"name":"Protein","weight":0.829843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protein"},{"name":"DNA","weight":0.799199,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DNA"},{"name":"Mitochondrial DNA","weight":0.790327,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mitochondrial_DNA"},{"name":"Mitochondrion","weight":0.72904,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mitochondrion"},{"name":"Mouse","weight":0.716131,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mouse"},{"name":"Mutation","weight":0.705743,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mutation"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.701843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Diet (nutrition)","weight":0.600225,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diet_(nutrition)"},{"name":"Nuclear DNA","weight":0.570586,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_DNA"},{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.54001,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Med